## Developer Layer — Structural Encoding (7, 8, 9)

To extend beyond human-readable encoding, Alphanumeria introduces a developer layer using structural symbols.

Digits:
7, 8, 9

---

## Core Rules

7 → start  
8 → separator (space / AND)  
9 → end  

---

## Purpose

This layer enables:
- structured encoding
- machine-readable parsing
- consistent message boundaries
- programmable extensions

---

## Example

Plain:
HELLO WORLD

Level 1:
H2LL4 W4RLD

Developer Layer:
7H2LL48W4RLD9

---

## Breakdown

- 7 → start of sequence  
- H2LL4 → HELLO  
- 8 → separator (space)  
- W4RLD → WORLD  
- 9 → end of sequence  

---

## Identity Example (ONID)

Plain:
BERNARD FREEMAN

Level 1:
B2RN1RD FR22M1N

Developer Layer:
7B2RN1RD8FR22M1N9

---

## System Design

Alphanumeria operates on two layers:

- 1–6 → human-readable meaning  
- 7–9 → structural / developer layer  

This creates a dual system:
- visible meaning
- encoded structure

---

## Design Principles

- deterministic
- minimal
- extensible
- readable + programmable

---

## Vision

The developer layer allows Alphanumeria to evolve into:

- a structured identity system  
- a lightweight communication protocol  
- a human-machine interaction layer  

---

Meaning is not only preserved.  
It becomes structured.
